<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05582</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT CREATING A CRIMINAL JUSTICE REFORM COMMISSION CHARGED WITH THE INVESTIGATION AND PREVENTION OF WRONGFUL CONVICTIONS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : “ Preventing Wrongful Conviction Act ”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : 
Provides for the nine-member composition of the Commission and its corresponding duties; Proposes reforms to minimize the likelihood of wrongful convictions, bolster public confidence in the criminal justice system, and ensure that the administration of criminal justice is fair, accurate and reliable.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SUANSING, HORACIO JR. P., SUANSING, ESTRELLITA B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-05-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE ON 2017-05-10</td></tr></table>